 <p><img src="/joomla/images/donation.jpg" alt="donation" width="500" height="273" style="margin: 8px; float: right;"></p>
<p><span style="color: #222222; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Every year the staff at The Edge Academy and Akros MIddle School donates $20 to be able to wear jeans on Fridays during the school year. The staff picks a charity to donate the money to that is making  a difference in the community of Akron. This year the staff decided to donate the funds collected, to Christ Child Charities of Akron. Each year Christ Child Charities of Akron help our families by donating uniforms to students in need. Christ child provides uniform pants, shirts, and often winter coats to over 15 families each year. The staff collected a total of $700 and the funds raised were matched by Dave Dudas the co-founder of The Edge Academy and Akros Middle School for a total donation of $1,400.</span></p>
